♪

1:09:26.733 --> 1:09:29.030
- Have you heard
of this Portuguese guy,

1:09:29.065 --> 1:09:31.472
Fernando Pessoa?

1:09:31.507 --> 1:09:34.134
- Is he on the Blue Jays?

1:09:34.169 --> 1:09:35.938
- No, he's a poet.

1:09:35.973 --> 1:09:38.347
This is his book.

1:09:38.382 --> 1:09:41.141
He's dead now.
He killed himself.

1:09:41.176 --> 1:09:45.783
- Oh, brother.
Who hasn't?

1:09:45.818 --> 1:09:49.886
- Just listen
to this, though.

1:09:49.921 --> 1:09:54.561
"In the plausible intimacy
of approaching evening,

1:09:54.596 --> 1:09:57.366
"as I stand waiting
for the stars to begin

1:09:57.401 --> 1:09:59.797
"at the window
of this fourth-floor room

1:09:59.832 --> 1:10:02.371
"that looks out on the infinite,

1:10:02.406 --> 1:10:06.540
"my dreams move to the rhythm
required by long journeys

1:10:06.575 --> 1:10:09.444
"to countries as yet unknown,

1:10:09.479 --> 1:10:14.108
"or to countries that are simply
hypothetical or impossible."

1:10:19.918 --> 1:10:21.951
- I just remembered
how your sister's smile

1:10:21.986 --> 1:10:24.085
is exactly like her father's.

1:10:28.696 --> 1:10:30.091
I never...

1:10:30.126 --> 1:10:34.260
I never think about it,
and then I'll see her and--

1:10:34.295 --> 1:10:35.965
whoa!
Oh...

1:10:41.742 --> 1:10:46.008
- Oh, Elfrieda!

1:10:53.886 --> 1:10:56.590
- It's okay, Mom.

1:10:56.625 --> 1:10:57.657
It's okay.

1:10:59.155 --> 1:11:03.630
- Oh, God.
Oh...

1:11:03.665 --> 1:11:06.259
Oof!

1:11:10.067 --> 1:11:11.968
- Hello?

1:11:12.003 --> 1:11:12.936
Oh, hi.

1:11:16.480 --> 1:11:19.305
Okay, yeah.

1:11:19.340 --> 1:11:21.846
We'll be there.

1:11:21.881 --> 1:11:24.486
Bye-bye.

1:11:24.521 --> 1:11:26.785
That was Nic.

1:11:26.820 --> 1:11:28.589
He said they're
letting Elf go home

1:11:28.624 --> 1:11:30.657
from the hospital Friday.

1:11:32.353 --> 1:11:33.825
- No.

1:11:35.862 --> 1:11:38.434
No, they can't.

1:11:38.469 --> 1:11:41.063
♪

