♪

1:11:45.102 --> 1:11:49.071
♪

1:11:49.106 --> 1:11:53.482
♪

1:11:53.517 --> 1:11:57.486
♪

1:11:57.521 --> 1:11:59.081
♪

1:11:59.116 --> 1:12:01.952
- It's been going
really well with the doctor,

1:12:01.987 --> 1:12:04.020
and for the first time
in such a long time

1:12:04.055 --> 1:12:05.659
I've been thinking
so much about my music

1:12:05.694 --> 1:12:07.397
and how I have
to get back to playing,

1:12:07.432 --> 1:12:10.829
which is why I called Claudio
and I confirmed the tour.

1:12:12.899 --> 1:12:16.131
- I know it's the right
thing for me to do.

1:12:16.166 --> 1:12:19.167
We finally feel like
I'm back on track.

1:12:21.270 --> 1:12:23.336
- Dr. Johns?

1:12:23.371 --> 1:12:24.909
Dr. Johns.
DR.- Yes?

1:12:24.944 --> 1:12:26.944
- She...
she's not ready.

1:12:26.979 --> 1:12:30.948
She's pretending to be
normal, sane, cured,

1:12:30.983 --> 1:12:33.082
and I'm sure you're thinking,
"Okay, let's free up a bed.

1:12:33.117 --> 1:12:34.622
"Let's let this one go,"
but I am...

1:12:34.657 --> 1:12:38.494
Um, I'm begging you,

1:12:38.529 --> 1:12:40.221
please don't do that.

1:12:40.256 --> 1:12:42.432
DR.- She's on
the right path,

1:12:42.467 --> 1:12:44.665
and it's very important for
the patient to feel empowered

1:12:44.700 --> 1:12:46.436
by being allowed
to make big decisions.

1:12:46.471 --> 1:12:48.504
- Well, one big
decision she could make

1:12:48.539 --> 1:12:50.297
would be the decision
to kill herself,

1:12:50.332 --> 1:12:51.705
and we can assume
that nobody wants

1:12:51.740 --> 1:12:53.872
her to make that
decision, right?

1:12:53.907 --> 1:12:55.874
Last week,
she's completely depressed.

1:12:55.909 --> 1:12:58.041
Asked me to take her to
a suicide clinic in Switzerland,

1:12:58.076 --> 1:13:01.781
and this week,

1:13:01.816 --> 1:13:04.410
what, she's just better?

1:13:04.445 --> 1:13:05.917
For what reason?

1:13:05.952 --> 1:13:07.754
DR.- She's agreed
to take her medications,

1:13:07.789 --> 1:13:09.525
book follow-up appointments,
so I have to give her

1:13:09.560 --> 1:13:12.022
the benefit of the doubt.

1:13:12.057 --> 1:13:15.289
I've seen many patients leave
here in worse shape than her

1:13:15.324 --> 1:13:18.094
and yet thrive once
they return to their lives.

1:13:28.304 --> 1:13:32.372
ELF V.O.: Ah,
solving that question

1:13:32.407 --> 1:13:35.683
brings the priest
and the doctor,

1:13:35.718 --> 1:13:38.048
in their long coats,

1:13:38.083 --> 1:13:40.347
running over the fields.

1:13:40.382 --> 1:13:43.922
♪

1:13:55.133 --> 1:13:58.805
♪

1:13:58.840 --> 1:14:01.874
♪

1:14:01.909 --> 1:14:03.645
♪

1:14:34.073 --> 1:14:37.305
- Well, I'm having serious
caffeine withdrawal.

1:14:37.340 --> 1:14:41.342
This cast itches like hell.

1:14:41.377 --> 1:14:42.981
- Your surgery
is at 6 tomorrow?

1:14:43.016 --> 1:14:45.654
- Yes.

1:14:45.689 --> 1:14:47.348
- You nervous?

1:14:47.383 --> 1:14:49.856
- No.

1:14:49.891 --> 1:14:52.826
If your mother can
survive heart surgery,

1:14:52.861 --> 1:14:54.355
well, so can I.

1:14:57.294 --> 1:14:59.998
- Alright.
I better go.

1:15:00.033 --> 1:15:02.737
I'll let you get some rest.

1:15:10.307 --> 1:15:12.340
- We're Loewens.

1:15:12.375 --> 1:15:15.046
Don't ever forget that, Yoli.

1:15:15.081 --> 1:15:18.511
We're lions!

1:15:18.546 --> 1:15:20.513
- Sure.

1:15:20.548 --> 1:15:25.386
♪

1:15:25.421 --> 1:15:28.730
♪

1:15:28.765 --> 1:15:31.898
♪

1:15:31.933 --> 1:15:35.462
YOLI V.O.: My aunt's
surgery is over.

1:15:35.497 --> 1:15:39.367
The operation had gone well.

1:15:39.402 --> 1:15:42.843
The doctor was pleased
and told us so.

1:15:42.878 --> 1:15:46.374
And then her organs
started to fail,

1:15:46.409 --> 1:15:48.508
one by one.

1:15:59.620 --> 1:16:01.796
- Is this almost
too much, Mom?

1:16:05.428 --> 1:16:06.900
- Almost.

1:16:12.105 --> 1:16:15.403
♪

1:16:15.438 --> 1:16:18.406
♪

1:16:18.441 --> 1:16:21.343
- Tina was a sensation.

1:16:21.378 --> 1:16:24.720
She adored big hats
with wide brims.

1:16:24.755 --> 1:16:28.251
Whistles followed her
down the street.

1:16:28.286 --> 1:16:33.124
She loved road trips,
talking late into the night,

1:16:33.159 --> 1:16:36.897
bear hugs, and good deals.

1:16:36.932 --> 1:16:39.702
She was a fiercely devoted wife

1:16:39.737 --> 1:16:44.135
and mom and aunt

1:16:44.170 --> 1:16:46.643
and big sister to me.

1:16:50.506 --> 1:16:52.979
When my wedding veil
caught on fire,

1:16:53.014 --> 1:16:56.543
I was signing the registry
and I was too close to a candle,

1:16:56.578 --> 1:16:59.986
and she bolted to her house,
grabbed her own veil,

1:17:00.021 --> 1:17:01.955
ran back to the church,
and plopped it on my head

1:17:01.990 --> 1:17:05.761
without hardly missing a beat.

1:17:05.796 --> 1:17:09.897
But her forte was coffee.

1:17:09.932 --> 1:17:11.734
On the day before she died,

1:17:11.769 --> 1:17:15.936
she asked me to please bring her
some good, strong coffee.

1:17:15.971 --> 1:17:18.334
When it finally arrived...

1:17:18.369 --> 1:17:20.842
Oh my!

1:17:20.877 --> 1:17:23.680
- She was
not able to drink it.

1:17:27.114 --> 1:17:31.083
Tina, we will miss not only
your many helpful ways

1:17:31.118 --> 1:17:35.417
but your positive spirit
spreading love and goodwill.

1:17:37.487 --> 1:17:40.059
You were the last of the lions.

1:17:44.296 --> 1:17:46.230
Rest in peace.

1:17:46.265 --> 1:17:49.365
♪

1:17:49.400 --> 1:17:52.808
YOLI V.O.: Life's always
teaching us lessons.

1:17:52.843 --> 1:17:54.810
Just because someone
is playing with the ashes

1:17:54.845 --> 1:17:56.537
of your protagonist

1:17:56.572 --> 1:18:00.310
doesn't mean you stop
telling the story.

1:18:00.345 --> 1:18:03.445
- And so,
I was standing in line

1:18:03.480 --> 1:18:07.515
outside the Notre-Dame Basilica,
waiting for the service.

1:18:07.550 --> 1:18:10.023
There were over
3,000 in attendance.

1:18:10.058 --> 1:18:12.223
Oh...

1:18:12.258 --> 1:18:15.864
And the man in front of me
asks me where I'm from,

1:18:15.899 --> 1:18:19.164
and he couldn't believe
I came so far for the funeral.

1:18:19.199 --> 1:18:22.134
- He was your hero.

1:18:22.169 --> 1:18:25.632
- In spite of his
many flaws, yes, he...

1:18:25.667 --> 1:18:28.470
he was my hero.

1:18:28.505 --> 1:18:32.474
And so, we began talking

1:18:32.509 --> 1:18:34.850
and we had the loveliest
conversation about Trudeau,

1:18:34.885 --> 1:18:38.216
his eccentricities, his gifts,

1:18:38.251 --> 1:18:40.889
his life.

1:18:40.924 --> 1:18:44.585
And then the strangest
thing happened:

1:18:44.620 --> 1:18:48.930
the man invited me
to a party at his house.

1:18:48.965 --> 1:18:52.901
And it was a very fancy house
in a very fancy neighbourhood,

1:18:52.936 --> 1:18:55.596
with champagne.

1:18:55.631 --> 1:18:57.235
- Oh!

1:18:57.270 --> 1:19:00.238
- Imagine me at
a complete stranger's house.

1:19:02.704 --> 1:19:05.408
Did you have
a glass of champagne?

1:19:05.443 --> 1:19:06.816
- Oh, no.

1:19:06.851 --> 1:19:08.950
Oh, no.

1:19:08.985 --> 1:19:10.446
No.

1:19:12.648 --> 1:19:13.988
No.

1:19:28.466 --> 1:19:29.597
Hello?

1:19:29.632 --> 1:19:31.104
- Have you spoken
with her today?

1:19:31.139 --> 1:19:32.732
- No, but Nic's there.

1:19:32.767 --> 1:19:36.604
- I know, I just wish they'd
answer it or text or whatever.

1:19:36.639 --> 1:19:38.672
I feel like a needy girlfriend.

1:19:38.707 --> 1:19:40.212
I can't stop calling.

1:19:40.247 --> 1:19:42.115
- Yeah,
I'm the overbearing mother.

1:19:42.150 --> 1:19:44.810
Whenever I stop by,
she gives me a look that says,

1:19:44.845 --> 1:19:46.614
"I'm not fooled by you.

1:19:46.649 --> 1:19:49.122
"I know you're
checking up on me."

1:19:49.157 --> 1:19:52.323
But it's impossible not to.

1:19:55.031 --> 1:19:58.967
♪

